observations.recommendation:
We recommended tha
 Direct the Committee to conduct physical count of properties and come up with the Report on Physical Count of PPE;
 Direct the Municipal Inventory Committee to attend training on Property and Supply Management in order to acquire knowledge on the conduct of physical count of PPE;
 Direct the Municipal Accountant to reconcile its records with the GSO records and prepare the physical inventory report for submission to COA.
 Require the Municipal Accountant to maintain a Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Card complete as to the data of acquisition, description, custody, estimated life, rate of depreciation disposal and other information about the properties based on the source documents of the transactions. Also, drop from the books of accounts the unserviceable properties after the Waste Material Report and the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property are duly approved and evaluated by COA.
